Create Button click counter app
---

âœ… S.Q.I. Breakdown

S â†’ Structure (HTML + CSS):

Basic structure me ek button aur ek counter number show hoga.

Q â†’ Query (JavaScript targets):

Button element ko select karenge

Counter element ko select karenge


I â†’ Implementation (Logic + Events):

Jab button click ho â†’ counter number +1 badhe

Event listener lagayenge

Value update karenge innerText se



---

ðŸ’» Final Output:

A button jis par har click pe count increase ho jaaye:

You clicked 0 times
[ Click Me ]


---

âœ… Code (HTML + CSS + JS in one file):

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>Button Click Counter</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 40px;
      background-color: #f0f0f0;
    }
    h2 {
      font-size: 24px;
    }
    button {
      padding: 10px 20px;
      font-size: 18px;
      cursor: pointer;
      margin-top: 10px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h2>You clicked <span id="count">0</span> times</h2>
  <button id="clickBtn">Click Me</button>

  <script>
    // Q â†’ Query
    const countSpan = document.getElementById('count');
    const clickBtn = document.getElementById('clickBtn');

    // I â†’ Implementation
    let counter = 0;
    clickBtn.addEventListener('click', function() {
      counter++;
      countSpan.innerText = counter;
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>


